---

6. Control Loop Architecture

Kubernetes works using control loops.

Controller logic:

desired state
      ↓
compare
      ↓
current state
      ↓
take action

Example:

Deployment wants:

replicas = 3

Controller loop:

check pods
if pods < 3
create pod

This runs continuously.


---

7. OpenShift Operator Framework

OpenShift platform components are managed by Operators.

Example operators:

cluster-version-operator
machine-config-operator
ingress-operator
authentication-operator
image-registry-operator

Operator logic:

Watch resource
      ↓
Detect change
      ↓
Run reconciliation
      ↓
Apply configuration

Example:

Cluster upgrade triggered.

ClusterVersionOperator
      ↓
Upgrade Operators
      ↓
Upgrade control plane
      ↓
Upgrade nodes


