2. Detailed Packet Flow Inside OVN-Kubernetes

OpenShift uses OVN-Kubernetes as the default CNI.

Based on:

Open vSwitch

Open Virtual Network



---

OVN Core Components

Node processes:

ovn-controller
ovs-vswitchd
ovsdb-server

Cluster components:

ovn-northd
ovn-nbdb
ovn-sbdb

Databases:

NBDB (Northbound DB)
SBDB (Southbound DB)


---

Pod Networking Creation

When a pod starts:

kubelet
   ↓
CNI request
   ↓
OVN plugin
   ↓
create logical port
   ↓
attach veth interface

Pod gets IP from cluster CIDR.

Example:

10.128.2.5


---

Packet Flow (Pod → Pod different node)

Pod A
 │
 ▼
veth interface
 │
 ▼
OVS bridge (br-int)
 │
 ▼
Geneve tunnel encapsulation
 │
 ▼
physical NIC
 │
 ▼
remote node
 │
 ▼
OVS bridge
 │
 ▼
veth pair
 │
 ▼
Pod B

Encapsulation protocol:

Geneve UDP 6081


---

Service Packet Flow

If using ClusterIP:

Pod
 │
 ▼
iptables/OVN load balancing
 │
 ▼
selected backend pod

OVN implements load balancing using logical flows.


