5. How kubelet Communicates with CRI-O

CRI-O implements Kubernetes Container Runtime Interface (CRI).

Communication uses:

gRPC over Unix socket

Socket path:

/var/run/crio/crio.sock


---

Communication Architecture

kubelet
  │
  │ gRPC (CRI API)
  ▼
CRI-O
  │
  ▼
OCI runtime (runc)
  │
  ▼
Linux kernel


---

Example CRI Calls

When pod starts:

RunPodSandbox
CreateContainer
StartContainer


---

Pod creation flow

kubelet receives pod spec
      │
      ▼
RunPodSandbox
      │
      ▼
CreateContainer
      │
      ▼
StartContainer

CRI-O then:

pull image
create container rootfs
invoke runc


---

Container Creation Internals

Steps:

1 pull image
2 unpack rootfs
3 create namespaces
4 apply cgroups
5 start process

Kernel features used:

namespaces
cgroups
seccomp
SELinux


